  "worklog": "## 2026-03-30 13:08 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 1] V4.1 Day 1 Results: +$7.92 (3W/2L) + Indicator Logging Fix\n\n**Task:** Compile V4.1 Day 1 morning session results. Fix enhanced outcome logging.\n\n**V4.1 Morning Session (11:00-13:00 UTC):**\n- **Trades: 6 total** (5 logged in outcomes, 1 missing due to restart)\n- **Results: 4W/2L = 67% WR**\n- **Balance: $922.45 \u2192 $930.37 = +$7.92**\n- **12:43 clean trade (post-fix):** YES $12.10 @ 0.474 \u2192 \u2705 WIN (+$13.44 payout)\n  - OBI\u2705(+0.69), CVD\u2705, MACD\u2705, VWAP\u274c \u2014 VWAP disagreed but 12h = relaxed hour\n  - Copy bullish@100 \u2014 attention signal theory holds (high conf = WIN)\n\n**Bug fix #2: Indicator logging race condition**\n- `_last_indicators` was being read at OUTCOME time (5 min later), not TRADE time\n- By outcome check, `_last_indicators` was overwritten by subsequent `should_trade()` calls\n- Fix: capture indicators dict at trade execution, pass to `_check_outcome()` as frozen copy\n- Bot restarted at 13:10 with fix. Next trade will have full indicator data in outcomes.\n\n**Balance confirmed: $930.37** \u2014 PM payouts settled from 3 wins. Net positive day despite double-trade bug.\n\n**Copy signal analysis for today's trades:**\n| Trade | Copy Signal | OBI | Result |\n|-------|-------------|-----|--------|\n| 11:19 | bullish@84 | \u274c | \u274c LOSS |\n| 11:38 | bearish@100 | \u274c\u2192\u2705 | \u2705 WIN |\n| 12:43 | bullish@100 | \u2705 | \u2705 WIN |\n\n**Pattern confirmed:** High-conf copy (100) = WIN regardless of direction. Low-conf (84) = LOSS.\n\n## 2026-03-30 12:38 UTC \u2014 [Pillar 4] F&G/Price Divergence: Fear at 8, BTC Up 2.8%\n\n**Task:** Analyze why 12h produced zero trades. Understand F&G/price relationship.\n\n**Finding:**\n- **12h: zero trades.** 38 minutes of 100% bullish bias. Not a single negative reading. PM YES at 0.465 (market strongly pricing UP).\n- **BTC rallied $66,011 \u2192 $67,881 (+2.8%) while F&G = 8 (Extreme Fear)**\n- This is a classic \"wall of worry\" climb \u2014 maximum bearish sentiment, bullish price\n\n**Why our strategy struggles in this regime:**\n1. Our strategy is contrarian to ORDER FLOW (fading bearish bias)\n2. In an uptrend, order flow is persistently bullish \u2192 no bearish signals to fade\n3. When pullbacks do occur, they're shallow ($17 range) \u2192 noise, not signal\n4. The market is ALREADY contrarian to sentiment (price up despite fear) \u2014 there's no additional contrarian edge\n\n**Trade frequency analysis:**\n- Pre-V3 (Mar 20-26): 20.5 trades/day\n- Post-V3 (Mar 27-30): 3.25 trades/day\n- Today: 2 real signals in 1.5 active hours (double-fire bug inflated to 5 executions)\n\n**BTC context:**\n- Dropped $72K\u2192$65K (Mar 25-29), now bouncing\n- Current $67,857 = 41% of weekly range (mid-range, not overbought)\n- Key level: $68,042 (today's high) \u2014 break above = continuation, fail = pullback\n- 50% Fibonacci retrace of drop = $68,500\n\n**Decision:** No changes. Low trade days are expected in strong trends. Our edge is in RANGE-bound markets with oscillating bias. Today is trending bullish \u2014 patience is correct. The 19h/20h session may see different dynamics as US traders enter.\n",
